=head1 DESCRIPTION

Provides information about the association between a queue and a limit.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CreatedAt => Str

The Unix timestamp of the date and time that the association was
created.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CreatedBy => Str

The user identifier of the person that created the association.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> LimitId => Str

The unique identifier of the limit in the association.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> QueueId => Str

The unique identifier of the queue in the association.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

The status of task scheduling in the queue-limit association.

=over

=item *

C<ACTIVE> - Association is active.

=item *

C<STOP_LIMIT_USAGE_AND_COMPLETE_TASKS> - Association has stopped
scheduling new tasks and is completing current tasks.

=item *

C<STOP_LIMIT_USAGE_AND_CANCEL_TASKS> - Association has stopped
scheduling new tasks and is canceling current tasks.

=item *

C<STOPPED> - Association has been stopped.

=back



=head2 UpdatedAt => Str

